{
  "stem": "26140.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And very often, when after the war, I spoke to some Jewish people, and they said to me, well, nobody was informing us?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Maybe we were making too much business to bother about this.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that's how it goes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They must have-- somebody must have been making business.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there was-- there wasn't-- it was only a day journey.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we received some bread for one day's supply.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were packed 40 people.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was tight, but for that short journey, it wasn't too bad.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When the train got to Buchenwald, we were moved to a separate camp, where they tried to sort out where are we going to go and where we're going to work.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was still a bit better, Buchenwald, in that respect.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was an older camp than Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was-- there were a lot of political prisoners, Communists, which ruled the camp.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "With it being an established camp, there were no gas chambers as far as I know.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So it was a lot different.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the tide of war was so near, that the spirit of everybody was much different.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When it came the next-- next few days, we've seen the cannons being shot and so on, we knew that the end is near.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I don't think we were worried whether they might shoot us before they moved.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But somehow, that didn't happen.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because we heard that the SS were very keen on destroying people before they capitulate.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So that's why we were a bit worried.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the camp managed to get some weapon inside the camp to wait for that time when the American did not arrive, that we were not shot.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And also, the guards moved in the camp, were, most of them, Ukrainians, which collaborated with Germans.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
